<subSubSection id="B3E819AF002FD97BFF35E744FE570FD0" pageId="9" pageNumber="129" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="FB4D4A24002FD97BFF35E744FE570FD0" blockId="9.[136,778,1806,2085]" pageId="9" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis id="C9869636002FD97BFF35E744FEC30F35" bold="true" box="[189,324,1878,1904]" pageId="9" pageNumber="129">Etymology.</emphasis>
The genus name combines parts of Cretaceous and 
<taxonomicName id="3CF231A7002FD97BFEB3E768FE4E0FD1" authorityName="Schluter" authorityYear="1978" box="[315,457,1914,1940]" class="Insecta" family="Gallorommatidae" genus="Galloromma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C9869636002FD97BFEB3E768FE4E0FD1" box="[315,457,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="129">Galloromma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B3E819AF002FD97BFF35E78CFF720060" pageId="9" pageNumber="129" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="FB4D4A24002FD97BFF35E78CFF720060" blockId="9.[136,778,1806,2085]" pageId="9" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis id="C9869636002FD97BFF35E78CFEBF0FFD" bold="true" box="[189,312,1950,1976]" pageId="9" pageNumber="129">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Female antenna 14-segmented with 7- segmented funicle and 5-segmented loose (movably interconnected) clava. Pronotum reaching wing base or nearly so.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B3E819AF002FD97BFCD7E719FAD70068" pageId="9" pageNumber="129" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FB4D4A24002FD97BFCD7E719FAD70068" blockId="9.[810,1452,1803,2093]" pageId="9" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis id="C9869636002FD97BFCD7E719FC540F60" bold="true" box="[863,979,1803,1829]" pageId="9" pageNumber="129">Remarks.</emphasis>
New genus differs from the 
<typeStatus id="2449F486002FD97BFAA6E719FAD90F60" box="[1326,1374,1803,1829]" pageId="9" pageNumber="129">type</typeStatus>
genus of the family 
<taxonomicName id="3CF231A7002FD97BFC6EE73EFAB10F03" authority="Schluter, 1978" authorityName="Schluter" authorityYear="1978" box="[998,1334,1836,1862]" class="Insecta" family="Gallorommatidae" genus="Galloromma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C9869636002FD97BFC6EE73EFBF30F03" box="[998,1140,1836,1862]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="129">Galloromma</emphasis>
Schlüter, 
<quantity id="3C0AE7C1002FD97BFB76E73EFAB10F03" box="[1278,1334,1836,1862]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.02412" pageId="9" pageNumber="129" unit="in" value="1978.0">1978</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in more polymerous antenna (13-segmented with 4-segmented club in 
<taxonomicName id="3CF231A7002FD97BFC0AE77CFB970FCD" authorityName="Schluter" authorityYear="1978" box="[898,1040,1902,1928]" class="Insecta" family="Gallorommatidae" genus="Galloromma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C9869636002FD97BFC0AE77CFB970FCD" box="[898,1040,1902,1928]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="129">Galloromma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and pronotum apparently reaching wing bases (shortened posterolateral and far not reaching wing bases in 
<taxonomicName id="3CF231A7002FD97BFC64E7BDFBFD0F8C" authorityName="Schluter" authorityYear="1978" box="[1004,1146,1967,1993]" class="Insecta" family="Gallorommatidae" genus="Galloromma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C9869636002FD97BFC64E7BDFBFD0F8C" box="[1004,1146,1967,1993]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="129">Galloromma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="3CF231A7002FD97BFB15E7BDFB800FAE" authority="Ortega et al., 2011" authorityName="Ortega" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Gallorommatidae" genus="Galloromma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turolensis">
<emphasis id="C9869636002FD97BFB15E7BDFA2C0F8C" box="[1181,1451,1967,1993]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="129">Galloromma turolensis</emphasis>
Ortega 
<emphasis id="C9869636002FD97BFC09E7C3FC300FAF" box="[897,951,2000,2026]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="129">et al</emphasis>
., 2011
</taxonomicName>
from the Albian San Just amber in 
<collectingCountry id="83E50AB4002FD97BFCA2E7E3FCED004E" box="[810,874,2033,2059]" name="Spain" pageId="9" pageNumber="129">Spain</collectingCountry>
is similar to the 
<typeStatus id="2449F486002FD97BFBBEE7E0FBE10049" box="[1078,1126,2034,2060]" pageId="9" pageNumber="129">type</typeStatus>
species in above characters and that is why it is transferred to the new genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
